# Architecture Rules

Read [AGENTS.md](../AGENTS.md) before implementing features.

## Required workflow

1. Read relevant `docs/` file for the task area
2. Search [docs/components/component-index.md](../docs/components/component-index.md)
3. Search [docs/hooks/hooks-index.md](../docs/hooks/hooks-index.md)
4. Search [docs/utilities/utilities-index.md](../docs/utilities/utilities-index.md)
5. Check [docs/audits/redundancy-report.md](../docs/audits/redundancy-report.md)

## Never

- Create parallel animation systems (use GSAP via `@/lib/gsap`)
- Use `motion` / Framer Motion for new animations
- Bypass `TransitionLink` for internal navigation
- Add new pages in `src/sections/` (use `src/views/`)
- Hardcode theme colors (use CSS variables in `globals.css`)
- Delete redundant code without human approval

## Always

- Register new pages in `src/lib/pages.js`
- Use `PageTitle` + `.page-enter-fade` on views
- Use cursor `data-*` attributes for hover interactions
- Import scroll utilities from `@/lib/gsap`
- Update docs indexes when adding shared modules

## Key paths

- Architecture: `docs/architecture/overview.md`
- Animation: `docs/architecture/animation.md`
- Cursor API: `src/lib/cursor/README.md`
